text: Rogersville is a town in, and the county seat of, Hawkins County, Tennessee, United States. It was settled in 1775 by the grandparents of Davy Crockett, and is the second-oldest town in the state. The population of Rogersville as of the 2020 census was 4,671. ==References== Category:Towns in Tennessee Category:County seats in Tennessee Category:Tri-Cities, Tennessee
title: Rogersville, Tennessee
